exp_data.name: AzoAMP-2
exp_data.notes: I read the lifetime off the absorption thermal recovery plots in the SI. I did this by identifying the time at which (1 - 1/e) of the absorptiion change had taken place. I also plotted the change in absorption spectrum that you would get from my lifetime estimation. I also estimated the error of my reading.

This isn't as bad as their other molecule, but their reported dG still leads to an error relative to the actual measured lifetime. With their dG you'd get a lifetime of 7 hours, not the 48 days they reported.
